Biography

Egerton was born in 1930. He was the son of Joscelyn Coghill and Elizabeth Atkins. He passed away in 2000.

Sir Egerton James Nevill Tobias Coghill, 8th Bt. was born on 26 March 1930. He was the son of Sir Joscelyn Ambrose Cramer Coghill, 7th Bt. and Elizabeth Gwendoline Atkins. He married Gabrielle Nancy Ryder, daughter of Major Dudley Claud Douglas Ryder and Nancy Edith Baker, on 12 April 1958. He died on 23 September 2000 at age 70. Sir Egerton James Nevill Tobias Coghill, 8th Bt. usually went by his middle name of Toby. He was educated at Gordonstoun School, Elgin, Morayshire, Scotland. He was educated at Pembroke College, Cambridge University, Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England. He was a headmaster. He succeeded as the 8th Baronet Coghill, of Coghill, co. York [G.B., 1778] on 6 June 1983.
